an Storm 2 Shrines That Were Closed to Stop Coronavirus Spread |first=Jon |last=Gambrell A | name-list-format = vanc |agency=Associated Press |date=17 March 2020 |work=Time}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"newyorker\">{{cite web |url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak |title=How Iran Became A New Epicenter of the Coronavirus Outbreak |last1=Wright |first1=Robin | name-list-format = vanc |date=24 February 2020 |work=[[The New Yorker]]}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Corriere_20Jan\">{{cite web |url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_30/coronavirus-italia-corona-9d6dc436-4343-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml |title=Coronavirus: Primi due casi in Italia |date=31 January 2020 |trans-title=Coronavirus: First two cases in Italy |work=Corriere della sera |language=it |access-date=31 January 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"thelocal-flight\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200131/italy-suspends-all-china-flights-after-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-rome/ |title=Italy suspends all China flights as coronavirus cases confirmed in Rome |date=31 January 2020 |work=TheLocal.it |access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"ThomReut_IT_16cluster_21Feb\">{{cite news |last1=Anzolin |first1=Elisa |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |title=Coronavirus outbreak grows in northern Italy, 16 cases reported in one day |date=21 February 2020 |access-date=21 February 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200221225322/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |archive-date=21 February 2020 |agency=[[Thomson Reuters]] |last2=Amante |first2=Angelo | name-list-format = vanc}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"bbc-pm-2403\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-52012432 |title=Coronavirus: Strict new curbs on life in UK announced by PM |date=24 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |work=BBC News}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NEJMFirstCase\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Holshue ML, DeBolt C, Lindquist S, Lofy KH, Wiesman J, Bruce H, Spitters C, Ericson K, Wilkerson S, Tural A, Diaz G, Cohn A, Fox L, Patel A, Gerber SI, Kim L, Tong S, Lu X, Lindstrom S, Pallansch MA, Weldon WC, Biggs HM, Uyeki TM, Pillai SK | display-authors = 6 |title=First Case of 2019 Novel Coronavirus in the United States |journal=The New England Journal of Medicine |volume=382 |issue=10 |pages=929\u2013936 |date=March 2020 |pmid=32004427 |pmc=7092802 |doi=10.1056/NEJMoa2001191 |collaboration=Washington State 2019-nCoV Case Investigation Team}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Jan29WH\">{{cite press release |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/statement-press-secretary-regarding-presidents-coronavirus-task-force/ |date=29 January 2020 |access-date=15 March 2020 |publisher=White House |title=Statement from the Press Secretary Regarding the President's Coronavirus Task Force}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NYTControl\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/27/us/politics/us-coronavirus-pence.html |title=Pence Will Control All Coronavirus Messaging From Health Officials |date=27 February 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=13 March 2020 |quote=The White House moved on Thursday to tighten control of coronavirus messaging by government health officials and scientists, directing them to coordinate all statements and public appearances with the office of Vice President Mike Pence, according to several officials familiar with the new approach.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Burke2020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/14/world/churches-mosques-temples-coronavirus-spread/index.html |title=What churches, mosques and temples are doing to fight the spread of coronavirus |last1=Burke |first1=Daniel | name-list-format = vanc |date=14 March 2020 |publisher=CNN |access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Parke