{"title_page": "List of twin towns and sister cities in the Republic of Ireland", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}}\n{{Incomplete list|date=April 2020}}\nThis is a '''list of places in Ireland''' having standing links to local communities in other countries. In most cases, the association, especially when formalised by [[Local government in the Republic of Ireland|local government]], is known as \"[[Sister cities|town twinning]]\" (though other terms, such as \"partner towns\" or \"sister cities\" are sometimes used instead), and while most of the places included are towns, the list also comprises villages, cities, districts, counties, etc. with similar links.\n\n[[File:Sign showing Greystones, Ireland, as a twin city to Holyhead, Wales.jpg|thumb|Sign posted at the entrance of Greystones, Co. Wicklow, Ireland, stating that the city is twinned with Holyhead, in Wales.]]\n\nThe list is arranged by [[Provinces of Ireland|province]]; and then by the [[Counties of Ireland|county]]. It forms part of the larger [[list of twin towns and sister cities]].\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==Connacht==\n===County Galway===\n====Galway City====\n*[[Galway]]\n:{{flagicon|Denmark}}{{flagicon|North Jutland Region}} [[Aalborg]], [[North Jutland Region]], [[Denmark]] (1997)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\">{{cite web|title=Town Twinning|publisher=Galway City Council|url=https://www.galwaycity.ie/town-twinning-information|date=2020|accessdate=29 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|New Zealand}} [[Auckland]], [[Auckland Region]], [[New Zealand]] (2002)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/>\n:{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}{{flagicon|England}} [[Bradford]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom]] (1986)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/>\n:{{flagicon|United States}}{{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Cambridge, Massachusetts|Cambridge]], [[Massachusetts]], [[United States]] (1994)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/><ref name=\"U.S. Embassy\">{{cite web|title=Sister Cities|publisher=U.S. Embassy in Ireland|url=https://ie.usembassy.gov/our-relationship/policy-history/sister-cities/|date=2020|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|United States}}{{flagicon|Illinois}} [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], [[United States]] (1997)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/><ref name=\"U.S. Embassy\"/>\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Brittany}} [[Lorient]], [[Brittany]], [[France]] (1975)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/>\n:{{flagicon|United States}}{{flagicon|California}} [[Menlo Park, California|Menlo Park]], [[California]], [[United States]] (2015)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/>\n:{{flagicon|United States}}{{flagicon|Wisconsin}} [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]], [[United States]] (2001)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/><ref name=\"U.S. Embassy\"/>\n:{{flagicon|Canada}}{{flagicon|New Brunswick}} [[Moncton]], [[New Brunswick]], [[Canada]] (2002)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/>\n:{{flagicon|China}} [[Qingdao]], [[Shandong|Shandong Province]], [[China]] (1999)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/>\n:{{flagicon|United States}}{{flagicon|Washington}} [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], [[United States]] (1986)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/><ref name=\"U.S. Embassy\"/>\n:{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Stirling]], [[Scotland]], [[United Kingdom]] (2012)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/>\n:{{flagicon|United States}}{{flagicon|Missouri}} [[St. Louis]], [[Missouri]], [[United States]] (1977)<ref name=\"Galway City Council\"/><ref name=\"U.S. Embassy\"/>\n\n====Galway County====\n*[[Athenry]]\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Brittany}} [[Quimperl\u00e9]], [[Brittany]], [[France]] (2004)<ref name=\"Athenry-Quimperl\u00e9\">{{cite web|title=Town Twinning|publisher=Athenry Parish Heritage Archive|url=https://athenryparishheritage.com/town-twinning/|date=2004|accessdate=29 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|Canada}}{{flagicon|Newfoundland and Labrador}} [[Renews-Cappahayden]], [[Newfoun