ell|publisher=Wicklow People|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/wicklowpeople/news/musical-extravaganza-planned-to-mark-twinning-with-eichenzell-27859181.html|date=27 January 2011|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|\u00cele-de-France}} [[Montigny-le-Bretonneux]], [[\u00cele-de-France]], [[France]] (1993)<ref name=\"Wicklow County Council\"/><ref name=\"Wicklow-Montigny-le-Bretonneux\">{{cite web|title=Wicklow|publisher=Montigny-le-Bretonneux|url=https://www.montigny78.fr/decouvrir-montigny/jumelages/wicklow.htm|date=2020|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}{{flagicon|Wales}} [[Porthmadog]], [[Wales]], [[United Kingdom]] (2006)<ref name=\"Wicklow County Council\"/><ref name=\"Wicklow-Porthmadog\">{{cite web|title=Twinning is official after the signing of charter|publisher=Wicklow People|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/wicklowpeople/news/twinning-is-official-after-the-signing-of-charter-27833587.html|date=6 September 2006|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Munster==\n\n===County Clare===\n*[[Ennis]]\n:{{Flagicon|United States}}{{Flagicon|Arizona}} [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], [[Arizona]], United States<ref name=\"US embassy list\"/>\n\n===County Cork===\n\n====Cork City====\n*[[Cork (city)|Cork]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.corkcity.ie/en/council-services/councillors-and-democracy/twinning/twinning.html |title=Twinning |date=8 December 2019}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n:{{flagicon|GER}} [[Cologne]], Germany (1988)\n:{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Coventry]], England, United Kingdom (1969)\n:{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Rennes]], [[Brittany]], France (1982)\n:{{flagicon|USA}} [[San Francisco]], California, United States (1984)\n:{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Swansea]], Wales, United Kingdom (1994)\n:{{flagicon|PRC}} [[Shanghai]], China (2005)\n\n====County Cork====\n*[[Clonakilty]]\n:{{flagicon|GER}} [[Waldaschaff]], Germany<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clontwinning.com/ |title=Home |website=www.clontwinning.com |acc