an Twinning\"/><ref name=\"Ballybay-Osterhofen\">{{cite web|title=Ballybay and Osterhofen twinning to be further developed by\u2008Municipal District|publisher=The Northern Standard|url=http://www.northernstandard.ie/2015/06/26/ballybay-and-osterhofen-twinning-to-be-further-developed-by%E2%80%88municipal-district/|date=26 June 2015|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n*[[Carrickmacross]]\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Brittany}} [[Carhaix-Plouguer]], [[Brittany]], [[France]] (1996)<ref name=\"Monaghan Twinning\"/><ref name=\"Carrickmacross-Carhaix-Plouguer\">{{cite web|title=Jumelages|publisher=Ville de Carhaix-Plouguer|url=http://www.ville-carhaix.bzh/accueil_carhaix/vivre_a_carhaix/jumelages|date=2020|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n*[[Castleblayney]]\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Occitanie}} [[Marseillan, H\u00e9rault|Marseillan]], [[Occitanie]], [[France]] (2013)<ref name=\"Monaghan Twinning\"/><ref name=\"Castleblayney-Marseillan\">{{cite web|title=Mayors Sign Town Council Charter in Twinning of Castleblayney and Marseillan|publisher=Castleblayney|url=https://castleblayney.ie/index.php/2-uncategorised/8-town-twinning|date=2020|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Centre-Val de Loire}} [[Nogent-sur-Vernisson]], [[Centre-Val de Loire]], [[France]] (2006)<ref name=\"Castleblayney-Nogent-sur-Vernisson\">{{cite web|title=Nogent, ville jumel\u00e9e avec...|publisher=Nogent-sur-Vernisson|url=https://www.nogentsurvernisson.fr/nogent-jumelage-castleblayney_fr.html|date=2020|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n*[[Tydavnet]]\n:{{flagicon|Belgium}}{{flagicon|Flanders}} [[Geel]], [[Flanders]], [[Belgium]] (1992)<ref name=\"Monaghan Twinning\"/><ref name=\"Tydavnet-Geel\">{{cite web|title=Tydavnet \u2014 Gheel Twinning|publisher=Tydavnet|url=http://tydavnet.com/history-of-tydavnet-village/tydavnet-%e2%80%94-gheel-twinning/|date=2020|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n:a.{{Note|NoteA}}The [[Oise|Automne Villages]] are [[B\u00e9tha